crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects SEASPY malware used by UNC4841 in attacks against Barracuda ESG appliances exploiting CVE-2023-2868
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects Linux binaries that encode bytes by splitting them into upper and lower nibbles and mapping them to custom lookup tables, seen being used by SEASPY and Bluez backdoors
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: MalGamy (Nextron System)

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects suspicious Linux binaries using stack-based string manipulation techniques, which are often used to generate PTY (pseudo-terminal) device names for stealth or persistence, seen being used by SEASPY and Bluez backdoors
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: MalGamy (Nextron System)

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.
